The course is an 37 mile loop that takes you through scenic farms, around large dams and ponds.  The course is generally rolling with some nice short power climbs and fun sweeping decent.  There are two larger climbs around mile  15 and 23..

Google Address:  1000 Mapletown Rd, Greensboro, PA, 15338

From Pittsburgh, PA  Take I-79 south.  Get off exit 7 (Kirby, PA).  Take a left off exit onto Kirby Road.  Continue on Kirby road for a few miles till the road comes to a stop sign.  Then take a right turn onto Garards Fort Road.  In about 5 miles you will come to a 4 way intersection, go straight which becomes Mapletown Road.  Continue on to Mapletown and High School will be on your right.  Total Travel Time 1 hour 30 minutes

description:
Join Bicyclings editors and George Hincapie on scenic country roads
 
The third-annual Bicycling Fall Classic welcomes riders of all ability levels to ride 10, 25, 50 or 90 miles on our favorite roads amid Eastern Pennsylvanias forests, farms and rolling hills.
 
All riders will enjoy attentive on-course nutritional, mechanical and medical support; timing chips (with prizing for top climbers on the 50- and 90-mile courses); a Roubaix-style victory lap around the iconic Valley Preferred Cycling Center (T-Town velodrome) track; and a post-ride party with healthy lunch, free beer, live music, free massage, and more.
 
New for 2013, Bicycling will host a VIP reception with George Hincapie at Bear Creek Mountain Resort in Macungie, PA on Saturday, October 5 from 6:00-9:00PM, with a limited number of tickets available during registration.

title: Vertical Earth! Glen Park Mountain Bike Time Trial
description: This race will be a time trial format.  Riders will race against the clock on an approximately 7.5 mile course.  The Pocono Bike Club and Stroud Regional Open Space are sponsoring the event as a way to raise awareness for this unique property and to raise money for both non-profit organizations.  This will be a time trial race.  Racers will be sent out at 30-60 second increments and race against the clock.
course: Glen Park is situated in between the Brodhead Creek and Godfrey's Ridge in Stroudsburg, PA.  The riders can expect a mix of double track, single track, grass, and fire roads.  Racers will start off along an old trolley trail and enjoy some rolling terrain to the low point of the course along the Broadhead creek.  After some fun single and double track riders will ascend the most sustained climb in the race.  The climb will end with a fire road to recover.  Once on top of Godfrey's ride, there will be several sections of tight twisty single track.  Climbers will then descend the ridge into the Promised Land, an area of fast and twisty single track.  The end is near as racers navigate across the mountain and finally descend a rocky area to a fire road.  The finish will be in full view of spectators as the racers enter a ball field and have a 200 yard sprint across the field to the finish.
registration:
Registration is available on www.bikereg.com

Information is available: 
https://www.facebook.com/groups/596649593720283/
notes: This will be a time trail format.  Racers will be emailed a time when they will start their race.  The first racer will go off at 9AM.
directions:
Glen Park is conveniently located off of Interstate 80 in Stroudsburg, PA.  
From I-80 Eastbound: Exit 307, Park Avenue.  Make a left on to Park Avenue.  Make your first right on to Lennox St.  Go one block and make a right on to Broad Street.  Make a left on to Collins Street.  Follow Collins Street all the way to the end to Glen Park.  
From I-80 Westbound: Exit 307, Broad Street. Make a left on to Broad Street.  Go two blocks and turn left on to Collins Street.  Follow Collins Street all the way to the end to Glen Park.
**Glen Park is in a residential neighborhood.  Please drive slowly, stop at all stop signs, and park where directed to do so.**
